# Decision 002 – Progress Over Activity

## Status

Accepted

---

## Decision

LifeOS measures meaningful progress rather than activity volume.

Completing more tasks does not automatically represent greater growth.

The system should encourage users to pursue work that meaningfully advances their projects, skills, or experiences.

---

## Problem

Many productivity systems reward quantity.

This encourages users to break work into artificial tasks or complete easy activities simply to increase statistics.

---

## Rationale

Progress should represent personal development rather than busyness.

Growth depends on context, challenge, effort, and importance—not simply time spent or tasks completed.

---

## Trade-offs

Pros

* Encourages meaningful work.
* Discourages "gaming the system."
* Supports long-term personal growth.

Cons

* XP becomes more difficult to calculate.
* Requires thoughtful quest design.

---

## Consequences

Future XP calculations should consider personal growth rather than purely objective measurements.

Analytics should focus on learning and improvement instead of productivity alone.

